ld(div); // Append the new <li> element to the existing <ul> element movieList.appendChild(newLi); <\/script> </body> </html> \`\`\` In this example, we start with an existing \`<ul>\` element with the id \`\\"movie-list\\"\`. We use \`document.getElementById()\` to select this element. Next, we create a new \`<li>\` element using \`document.createElement(\\"li\\")\`. Within the \`<li>\` element, we create a \`<div>\` element using \`document.createElement(\\"div\\")\`. For the \`<h3>\` and \`<p>\` elements, we follow the same process, creating them with \`document.createElement()\` and setting their \`textContent\` values accordingly. Finally, we append the \`<h3>\` and \`<p>\` elements to the \`<div>\` element, and the \`<div>\` element to the \`<li>\` element. Then, we append the new \`<li>\` element to the existing \`<ul>\` element. This will add a new movie entry with the desired structure to the list dynamically using JavaScript."},{"prompt":"std::chrono::steady_clock::now()","completion":"std::chrono::steady_clock::now() is a function call that returns the current time point of the steady clock in the std::chrono library. The steady clock is a monotonic clock that cannot be adjusted and represents the time duration since an unspecified epoch. The now() function returns a std::chrono::time_point representing the current time."},{"prompt":"std::chrono::steady_clock::now() 获取的时间戳精度","completion":"std::chrono::steady_clock::now() 获取的时间戳精度取决于系统的实现。在大多数系统上，std::chrono::steady_clock 使用纳秒 (nanoseconds) 级别的精度，但也有可能是微秒 (microseconds) 或毫秒 (milliseconds) 级别的精度。这取决于操作系统和编译器的支持以及硬件性能。可以使用 std::chrono::steady_clock::period::num 和 std::chrono::steady_clock::period::den 获取时间戳的精确度，其中 num 表示时钟每秒的周期数，den 表示每秒的基本时间单位数。例如，如果 num 是 1，den 是 1000000000，表示时间戳的精度为纳秒级别。"},{"prompt":"如何计算两个时间的差值","completion":"要计算两个时间点的差值，可以使用 std::chrono::duration 类型来表示时间间隔，并使用 std::chrono::duration_cast 将时间间隔转换为所需的时间单位。 下面是一个示例，演示了如何计算两个时间点之间的差值，并以秒为单位输出： \`\`\`cpp #include <iostream> #include <chrono> int main() { // 获取起始时间点 auto start = std::chrono::steady_clock::now(); // 执行一些操作（这里只是为了模拟一段时间的消耗） std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::seconds(2)); // 获取结束时间点 auto end = std::chrono::steady_clock::now(); // 计算时间差（以秒为单位） std::chrono::duration<double> diff = end - start; // 将时间差输出为秒 std::cout << \\"Time difference: \\" << diff.count() << \\" seconds\\" << std::endl; return 0; } \`\`\` 在上述示例中，我们使用 std::chrono::steady_clock::now() 获取了起始时间点和结束时间点，然后使用运算符 - 计算了它们之间的差值。通过使用 std::chrono::duration 类型，我们可以灵活地将差值转换为所需的时间单位，这里我们使用 std::chrono::duration_cast 将差值转换为 double 类型的秒数。 输出结果将会显示从起始时间点到结束时间点的时间差，单位为秒。"},{"prompt":"怎么计算以毫秒为单位的时间差","completion":"要计算以毫秒为单位的时间差，可以将差值通过 \`std::chrono::duration_cast\` 转换为 \`std::chrono::milliseconds\` 类型。以下是一个示例： \`\`\`cpp #include <iostream> #include <chrono> int main() { // 获取起始时间点 auto start = std::chrono::steady_clock::now(); // 执行一些操作（这里只是为了模拟一段时间的消耗） std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1500)); // 获取结束时间点 auto end = std::chrono::steady_clock::now(); // 计算时间差（以毫秒为单位） auto diff = std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::milliseconds>(end - start); // 将时间差输出为毫秒 std::cout << \\"Time difference: \\" << diff.count() << \\" milliseconds\\" << std::endl; return 0; } \`\`\` 在上述示例中，\`std::chrono::milliseconds\` 用于表示时间差，并利用 \`std::chrono::duration_cast\` 将时间差转换为毫秒。最后，通过 \`count()\` 函数获取以毫秒为单位的时间差。 输出结果将会显示从起始时间点到结束时间点的时间差，单位为毫秒。"},{"prompt":"2e-07 时多杀","completion":"2e-07 表示的是一个科学计数法的数值，即2乘以10的-7次方，也就是0.0000002。这个值非常小，表示一个非常短的时间间隔。 如果用秒来表示这个时间间隔，则可以简单地将科学计数法的数值转换成正常的小数形式： 2e-07 秒 = 0.0000002 秒 这表示一个非常微小的时间间隔，几乎可以认为是几乎瞬间，可以说是非常短的时间。"},{"prompt":"Write a Legend of Korra fanfiction about Asami and Korra's relationship to Kuvira during her reign as the Great Uniter","completion":"Title: Embers of Redemption Chapter 1: Shadows of the Past Asami and Korra sat in silence, gazing out at Republic City from the rooftop of Air Temple Island. Their love had grown strong, yet a looming shadow of concern plagued their hearts: Kuvira's oppressive rule as the Great Uniter. \\"Korra,\\" Asami finally broke the silence, her voice tinged with worry. \\"What do we do about Kuvira? Her reign has brought so much pain and suffering to the Earth Kingdom.\\" Korra leaned back, resting her head on Asami's shoulder. \\"I know things seem bleak right now, but we can't lose hope. We've faced tough challenges before and come out stronger.\\" The Avatar's words were comforting, but Asami couldn't shake off the unease. They both knew that Kuvira's reign threatened not only the Earth Kingdom but their own lives as well. Asami's intellect told her they needed to find a way to stop Kuvira, but her heart told her to keep Korra safe above all else. Chapter 2: A Glimmer of Light One fateful evening, word reached Republic City that Kuvira planned to host an extravagant party—a display of her power and influence. Hoping to gather any information that could aid them in their fight against the Great Uniter, Asami persuaded Korra that attending the event might offer an opportunity. With a plan in place, Asami used her connections to secure invitations. Amidst the elaborate grandeur of Kuvira's palace, Asami and Korra discreetly searched for any trace of a weakness among the revelers. Their eyes met with a familiar face across the room: Kuvira's trusted advisor and former Beifong clan member, Bolin. Asami momentarily froze at the sight of her estranged friend, her heart sinking at the realization that Bolin was part of Kuvira's regime. Chapter 3: Chance Encounters Mustered up by determination and curiosity, Asami approached Bolin late that night in the corner of the party hall. \\"Bolin, it's been too long,\\" she said, mustering a friendly smile despite the uneasy circumstances. \\"How did you end up here with Kuvira?\\" Bolin's face seemed conflicted, reflecting both loyalty and regret. \\"Asami, Korra, I… I wanted to help. Kuvira promised to unify the Earth Kingdom, to make it strong and prosperous. But I didn't fully understand the cost.\\" Korra, having silently observed, couldn't contain her emotions any longer. \\"Bolin, we can't let her continue down this path. Innocent people are suffering.\\" Bolin nodded, then hesitantly shared a piece of troubling information. \\"There's a new weapon project under development—a spirit energy cannon. Kuvira plans to use it to cement her dominance.\\" Chapter 4: A Dangerous Gamble Determined to prevent Kuvira from unleashing further destruction, Asami, Korra, and Bolin secretly coordinated their efforts to sabotage the weapon project. Bolin's inside knowledge allowed them to navigate through the intricate network of Harumos, Kuvira's loyal engineers, undetected. Asami's technological skills proved indispensable, allowing her to disable and dismantle key components of the weapon while Korra and Bolin dealt with guards attempting to interfere. The trio knew their actions might not change Kuvira's overall iron grip, but it was a small victory— a glimmer of hope. Their successful disruption prompted Kuvira to increase security measures, further tightening her rule, and increasing tensions within her own ranks. Chapter 5: Redemption Beckons News of their sabotage spread throughout the Earth Kingdom, stirring whispers of defiance and rebellion. Korra realized that Kuvira's empire was built on fear and manipulation, and the people needed to see her for who she truly was. Asami, with her deep understanding of propaganda and media, saw an opportunity to expose Kuvira's corruption. By leveraging her technology and resources, she spread stories of Kuvira's oppressive rule, revealing the suffering she caused, burdening even her closest allies. Together, Asami and Korra worked tirelessly to support the formation of resistance movements, in the hopes that the oppressed would rally against the Great Uniter. Chapter 6: Embers of Hope In the final showdown, Asami, Korra, and Bolin joined forces with the united rebel factions across the Earth Kingdom. With their combined strength, they confronted Kuvira and her loyalists, determined to wrestle control from her iron grasp. As their fight raged on, Kuvira's inner circle began to question their blind allegiance, witnessing firsthand the devastation their leader inflicted. Slowly, cracks appeared in Kuvira's armor. In a climactic moment, Kuvira, weakened and isolated, faced the resolute gaze of Asami, Korra, and Bolin. They offered her a chance at redemption—a path back to the light she had strayed from. Torn between her ambitions and the remnants of her humanity, Kuvira made her choice. She surrendered, realizing that the true strength of a leader lies not in their dominance but in their ability to unite, nurture, and bring hope to those they serve. Epilogue: Rebuilding and Reconciliation Asami, Korra, and Bolin emerged from the ashes of Kuvira's oppressive reign, determined to rebuild the Earth Kingdom together. It would be a long journey filled with healing, forgiveness, and the rekindling of lost friendships. In the aftermath, Asami and Korra stood hand in hand, their love forged stronger through their shared struggle. They knew the harsh lessons Kuvira had taught them would forever remind them of the importance of compassion, understanding, and humility. And as Republic City thrived once more, its shores washed clean of Kuvira's darkness, the embers of redemption flickered brightly, reminding the world that even in the face of chaos, hope could be found."},{"prompt":"流体相似理论","completion":"流体相似理论是描述流体运动行为的一种理论模型。根据这一理论，当两个流体流动的条件相似时，它们的运动行为也会相似。 流体相似理论基于流体力学的基本方程，包括质量守恒方程、动量守恒方程和能量守恒方程。根据这些方程，可以推导出一些无量纲参数，例如雷诺数、马赫数和普朗特数等，用于描述流体流动的特征。 在实际应用中，流体相似理论可以帮助工程师设计模型实验，以研究流体流动的行为。通过调整实验中的流体性质、几何尺寸和流动速度等参数，使得实验中的无量纲参数与实际工程中的参数相似，从而实现对实际流体流动行为的模拟。 流体相似理论在众多领域中都有应用，包括空气动力学、海洋工程、化工工程和生物医学等。通过流体相似理论，人们可以更好地理解流体流动的行为，并为工程设计提供准确的参考。"},{"prompt":"流体相似理论的具体解释","completion":"流体相似理论是基于流体力学的一种理论模型，用于描述流体在不同条件下的运动行为。它假设当两个流体流动的条件相似时，它们的运动行为也会相似。 具体来说，流体相似理论是基于流体力学基本方程得出的一些无量纲参数和相似定律。无量纲参数是通过选择适当的长度、